.TH "lpfc_debugfs_dumpHBASlim_data" 9 "lpfc_debugfs_dumpHBASlim_data" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
lpfc_debugfs_dumpHBASlim_data \- Dump HBA SLIM info to a buffer
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" lpfc_debugfs_dumpHBASlim_data
.BI "(struct lpfc_hba *phba "  ","
.BI "char *buf "  ","
.BI "int size "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "phba" 12
The HBA to gather SLIM info from.
.IP "buf" 12
The buffer to dump log into.
.IP "size" 12
The maximum amount of data to process.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This routine dumps the current contents of HBA SLIM for the HBA associated
with \fIphba\fP to \fIbuf\fP up to \fIsize\fP bytes of data. This is the raw HBA SLIM data.

Return Value:
This routine returns the amount of bytes that were dumped into \fIbuf\fP and will
not exceed \fIsize\fP.
.SH "NOTES"
This routine will only dump up to 1024 bytes of data each time called and
should be called multiple times to dump the entire HBA SLIM.
